          "image_role": "content",
          "media": {
            "path": "resources/images/cooling-manifold-upscayl-2x-upscayl-lite-4x.jpg",
            "alt": "Cooling manifold_upscayl_2x_upscayl-lite-4x.png",
            "source_asset": "Cooling manifold_upscayl_2x_upscayl-lite-4x.jpg",
            "mime_type": "image/jpeg",
            "bytes": 42041,
            "dimensions": {
              "originalWidth": 796,
              "originalHeight": 1104
            }
          },
          "body_html": "<p>Managing severe thermal heat spots generated by next-generation silicon requires absolute mechanical and fluid engineering precision.</p><p>This module provides a comprehensive breakdown of how modern data centers implement leak-free fluid delivery at scale, and arms you with the ecosystem navigation tools needed to leverage public OCP designs, CAD models, and specifications for your own deployments. &nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "type": "quote",
          "variant": "d",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "LIGHT",
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "quote_html": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 2.1rem\"><em>Special thanks to Eduardo Estrada, PMTS System Architect at AMD, for his technical guidance and input, which were instrumental in the development of this course.</em></span></p>",
          "avatar": {
