              "originalWidth": 1680,
              "originalHeight": 295
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "type": "image",
          "variant": "text_aside",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1c1c1c",
            "image_size": "medium",
            "image_opacity": 0.5,
            "image_opacity_color": "#000000",
            "zoom_on_click": true,
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "image_role": "content",
          "media": {
            "path": "resources/images/orw-liquid-cooling-mechanics.jpg",
            "alt": "ORW Liquid cooling mechanics.jpg",
            "source_asset": "ORW Liquid cooling mechanics.jpg",
            "mime_type": "image/jpeg",
            "bytes": 264157,
            "dimensions": {
              "originalWidth": 1680,
              "originalHeight": 950
            }
          },
          "body_html": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 1.8rem\">Connecting heavy IT gear to high pressure liquid manifolds inside a fully populated rack requires automated precision to eliminate manual human errors and catastrophic leak risks.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 1.8rem\">Click through the graphic below to explore the three distinct mechanical phases of a Pivoting Blind Mate Coupling (PBMC) engagement.</span></p><p></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "type": "divider",
          "variant": "divider",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1c1c1c",
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          }
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "type": "labeled_graphic",
          "variant": "labeledgraphic",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1c1c1c",
            "zoom_on_click": true,
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3,
            "media_width": "1",
            "media_width_variant": "medium"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "The Pivot",
              "x": "14.9045163109189",
              "y": "51.73941798941799",
              "icon": "01",
              "description_html": "<p>Before the fluid seals meet, the coupling engages a brilliant mechanical pivot mechanism. This floating pivot automatically self centers the connection assembly, physically absorbing any angular misalignment or structural drag caused by the rigid, heavy liquid hoses attached to the rear of the node chassis.</p>"
            },
            {
              "title": "Managing Misalignment",
              "x": "50.04712785993304",
              "y": "56.962083281663354",
              "icon": "01",
              "description_html": "<p>As the heavy server node slides forward inside the structural Canister enclosure, the plug and receptacle fluid connectors approach each other deep within the rack frame. <br><br>At this initial phase, the hardware must dynamically compensate for standard manufacturing tolerances, physical frame flexing, and the immense gravitational weight of the server chassis.</p>"
            },
            {
              "title": "The Fluid Lock",
              "x": "89.04638381231399",
              "y": "51.42857142857142",
              "icon": "01",
              "description_html": "<p>In the final phase of insertion, the connectors slide cleanly together with a definitive mechanical click, establishing a completely sealed fluid path capable of handling high flow rates used to cool AI accelerators. <br><br>Once fully mated, the floating mechanism decouples mechanical adjusting tolerances from the primary seal area, ensuring a zero-leak lock without any manual intervention.</p>"
            }
          ],
          "media": {
            "path": "resources/images/untitled-design-40.jpg",
            "alt": "Untitled design (40).jpg",
            "source_asset": "Untitled design (40).jpg",
            "mime_type": "image/jpeg",
            "bytes": 62159,
            "dimensions": {
