    {
      "id": 6,
      "slug": "knowledge-check",
      "title": "Knowledge Check",
      "description_html": "",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "type": "text",
          "variant": "paragraph",
          "style": {
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "body_html": "<p style=\"line-height: 1.94118\"><span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-decoration: inherit\" data-color-scope=\"outer\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)\"><span>Test your knowledge from this module. Select the best answer for each question, then submit.</span></span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "type": "image",
          "variant": "full",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "LIGHT",
            "card_mode": "WHITE",
            "image_opacity": 0.5,
            "image_opacity_color": "#000000",
            "zoom_on_click": false,
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 0,
            "padding_bottom": 0,
            "custom_padding_top": 0,
            "custom_padding_bottom": 0,
            "entrance_animation": true
          },
          "image_role": "decorative",
          "media": {
            "path": "resources/images/black-banner-intro.png",
            "alt": "Black banner - intro.png",
            "source_asset": "Black banner - intro.png",
            "mime_type": "image/png",
            "bytes": 12283,
            "dimensions": {
              "originalWidth": 1680,
              "originalHeight": 295
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "type": "knowledge_check",
          "variant": "multiple_choice",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1e1e1e",
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "question_type": "multiple_choice",
          "question_html": "<p>What specific problem does the mechanical pivot mechanism inside the Pivoting Blind Mate Coupling (PBMC) solve during node insertion?</p>",
          "choices": [
            {
              "text_html": "<p>It converts alternating electrical current into direct current paths.</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>It automatically compensates for angular misalignment and heavy hose influence to prevent connector damage. </p>",
              "correct": true
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>It throttles the internal server fans when liquid flow rates fluctuate.</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>It locks the front loading server handles to prevent accidental extraction.</p>",
              "correct": false
            }
          ],
          "feedback_correct_html": "<p>Correct! The PBMC utilizes a precise mechanical pivot to absorb structural tolerance variables and heavy hose drag, guaranteeing a secure, self aligning connection every single time.</p>",
          "feedback_incorrect_html": "<p>Incorrect. The primary function of the pivot assembly is purely mechanical alignment. It dynamically absorbs angular tolerances and heavy hose influence to guide the fluid connectors into a perfect seal.</p><p></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "type": "knowledge_check",
          "variant": "multiple_choice",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1e1e1e",
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "question_type": "multiple_choice",
          "question_html": "<p>Which implementation serves as the highly optimized reference solution designed to validate the foundational 1200 millimeter ORW frame standard at scale?</p>",
          "choices": [
            {
              "text_html": "<p>Open Rack V1 History Template</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>Traditional 19-inch EIA Server Frame</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>The AMD Helios Reference Architecture</p>",
              "correct": true
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>Standard Air Cooled HPR Configuration</p>",
              "correct": false
            }
          ],
          "feedback_correct_html": "<p>Correct! Helios acts as a flagship reference instantiation, demonstrating how massive silicon footprints and complex fluid manifolds integrate perfectly within the expanded wide frame format.</p>",
          "feedback_incorrect_html": "<p>Incorrect. The Helios reference architecture is the primary platform developed to prove the horizontal volume and component integration of the open 1200 millimeter ORW specification.</p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "type": "knowledge_check",
          "variant": "multiple_choice",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1e1e1e",
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "question_type": "multiple_choice",
          "question_html": "<p>Where should an infrastructure operator go to locate open source CAD models, full engineering source files, and finalized community technical specifications for the Open Rack Wide framework?</p>",
          "choices": [
            {
              "text_html": "<p>Local hardware vendor private catalogs</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>Standard commercial search engine image repositories</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>General proprietary data center facility handbooks</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>The OCP  Contributions Database</p>",
              "correct": true
            }
          ],
          "feedback_correct_html": "<p>Correct! The OCP Contribution Database host complete, vendor neutral access to all base specifications, engineering files, and structural models for global community use.</p>",
          "feedback_incorrect_html": "<p>Incorrect. All official community specifications, accepted designs, and production ready CAD source files are hosted directly within the public, vendor neutral OCP Contribution Database.</p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "type": "image",
          "variant": "full",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "LIGHT",
            "card_mode": "WHITE",
            "image_opacity": 0.5,
            "image_opacity_color": "#000000",
